[1]
Date: Thu, 23 May 2002 11:21:22 -0700
From: Richard I Frankel <Richard.Frankel@med.va.gov>
Since methemoglobin is generated physiologically and is normally found in
the body, albeit at low levels, it is inaccurate to call it an abnormal
hemoglobin. What is abnormal is the quantity found in the blood.
--
Richard I Frankel MD MPH
Associate Chief of Staff for Education
VAMROC Honolulu
<Richard.Frankel@med.va.gov>
